se of the contribution of\nthe subdominant Askaryan effect in addition to the dominant geomagnetic\nemission. Subselecting events with a zenith angle greater than $70^{\\circ}$\nremoves most influence of the Askaryan emission, and, with limited statistics,\nwe found the polarization uncertainty is reduced to $1.3^{\\circ}$ (68%\ncontainment).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Dec 2021 18:49:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 3 Dec 2021 23:31:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 15 Dec 2021 02:18:22 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 29 Mar 2022 20:22:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-09"}
