e, a necessary condition for the operation of 1720 MHz OH masers is\na high ionization rate of molecular gas, $\\zeta_{H_2} \\gtrsim 10^{-15}$\ns$^{-1}$. We find that physical conditions conducive to the operation of both\nhydroxyl and methanol masers are cosmic ray ionization rate $\\zeta_{H_2}\n\\approx 10^{-15} - 3 \\times 10^{-15}$ s$^{-1}$, and a narrow range of shock\nspeeds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Dec 2021 14:35:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-15"}
